article:
'Green waste' is biodegradable waste that can be composed of garden or park
waste, such as grass or flower cuttings and hedge trimmings, as well as domestic
and commercial food waste. The differentiation green identifies it as high in
nitrogen, as opposed to ''brown'' waste, which is primarily carbonaceous.

Green waste is often collected in municipal curbside collection schemes or
through private waste management contractor businesses and subject to
independent audit.

.]]

Biogas captured from biodegrable green waste can be use as biofuel. Green waste
can be used as non food crop to produce cellulosic ethanol.
